  volume    = {5},
  abstract  = {Discusses efforts to end the global AIDS epidemic by 2030. Gains made in the control of the HIV epidemic are being lost. Those working in psychiatry, psychology, and global mental health can provide a leadership and public health-oriented role, directing and advising on the development, testing, and implementation of programmes capable of addressing the dual challenges of mental ill health and poor engagement in HIV testing and care. The shortage of mental health specialists in countries with the highest HIV burden demands the thoughtful allocation of such resources and underlines the importance of sustainable, culturally-appropriate, task-shifted and stepped-care frameworks, enriched with peer, family, and social support. (PsycINFO Database Record (c) 2018 APA, all rights reserved)},
